title: For Sale/Trade:  Mosin Carbine M38
postcontent: I'm sellling off my Mosin carbines, hate to let them go but want to finish my AR so it needs to go. The other is listed here also. This carbine is  Mosin M38. This is the first style carbine the Russians made, like most of the Carbines the Russians made during WWII they cut down a 91/30s because they had lots of them and wanted a smaller rifle. M38 didn't have bayonets like the later M44 so these are a little harder to find. This rifle doesn't have import markins so it made it to the USA between 1940s-1960s I like to think it was a soldier bring back but I can't be sure. The rifle shoots great and has spent most of the time I have had it in the safe. The only thing I know wrong is the cleaning rod is missing but I never use the rods that come with the rifles so it wasn't a issue for me. They can be bought online pretty cheap is someone wanted to replace it. I always cleaned it my Mosins 3 times(over 3 days) after shooting just in case of poor ammo. My price is based on the condition of the rilfe,the rareity of the M38 compared to the other carbines and no import markings. This isn't one of the cheap Type 53 chineese rifles that are beat up.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Mosin Carbine M44
postcontent: I'm sellling off 2 of my Mosin carbines, hate to let it go but want to finish my AR so they needs to go. I have the other carbine listed in another post.This Mosin Carbine is a M44. The first M44 carbines made, like most of the Carbines the Russians made during WWII they cut down a 91/30s because they had lots of them and wanted a smaller rifle. After the war they allowed some soviet contries to make new M44 based on the same rifle. The M44 has a swing out bayonet to help keep it from getting lost. This rifle has a Simons Shotgun long eye relief scope(3x9 I think), sling (not in photo), Matching serial number on Bolt, Mag plate, Reciever and Butt Plate, and Stock is a WWII stock because it doesn't have the metal inserts on the rear sling holes and small ones on the front. My price is based on the condition of the rilfe, and the rareity of the M44 compared to the other carbines. This isn't one of the cheap Type 53 chineese rifles that are beat up. It isn't often to find Russian rifles with matching Serial numbers. Rifle shoots great and holds groups very well. I always cleaned it my Mosins 3 times(over 3 days) after shooting just in case of poor ammo. The price is based on the condition of the rifle, scope, and rarity.

title: For Sale:  Blackbird SK-5 with Hedgehog Leatherworks Sheath
postcontent: This is a "used" Blackbird SK-5, but the blade was warranty replaced by Ontario Knife Company last year. It has the original Micarta handle scales that you can't get anymore, Ontario switched to G10 Scales on this knife a couple years ago. The Micarta scales show a little scuffing/darkening from the sheath and light use, but are in perfect condition otherwise. The blade is unused/untouched since the warranty replacement and still has the factory edge. Also included is the original box, original tan sheath, and the warranty repair paperwork. Below are the knife specs. The Hedgehog Leatherworks sheath is the original version of the basic model. It has a little scuffing on the leather from use, but that's very minor. It also has some minor scuffing on the snaps. The sheath functions perfectly and I have had no issues with it. Hedgehog Leatherworks is owned and operated by Paul Sheiter, he designed the Blackbird SK-5 and makes the best sheath available for this knife, in my opinion. Below are the sheath specs. Ontario Blackbird SK-5:The award winning Black Bird series was designed by custom designer and sheath-maker Paul Sheiter for maximum performance with an elegant simplicity and the signature elements of a center point blade, straight back profile and a flat heel for maximum utility. Featuring high quality 154 CM stainless steel and tan Micarta handle, the Black Bird variants come in either a silver finish or with a special operations capable (SOC) powder coating for added durability. All Black Bird models include a MOLLE compatible sheath. OVERALL LENGTH: 10 in (25.4 cm)LOCK TYPE: FixedHARDNESS: 58-60 HRCEDGE TYPE: PlainCOUNTRY OF ORIGIN: United States of AmericaHANDLE COLOR: TanBLADE GRIND: Full Flat TaperBLADE FINISH: MirrorBLADE COLOR: SilverBLADE THICKNESS: 0.138 in (0.351 cm)BLADE MATERIAL: 154 CM Stainless SteelBLADE LENGTH: 5 in (12.7 cm)HANDLE MATERIAL: MicartaSHEATH MATERIAL: NylonSHEATH COLOR: TanSHEATH TYPE: MOLLE Compatible Hedgehog Leatherworks Sheath:25 Year WarrantyIf anything goes wrong with your Hedgehog Leatherworks product, we will fix or replace it for a period of 25 years after the date it was delivered to your doorstep. Just let us know what happened and we will make it right. The only way to void your warranty is to intentionally abuse the product or modify it. Otherwise, we stand behind it no matter what. We are known for our obsessive commitment to quality... so if we are fortunate enough to earn your business, you can bet we will work to keep it. Handed Crafted in the USAWe are a small team of craftsmen who feel a true sense of purpose in keeping "USA Handmade" alive. We never rush a product and we obsess about the smallest details. If we mess up along the way, we start over and keep working until it is perfect. Sometimes that can be painful, but we believe that "good enough is never good enough" and that's why we only ship our best work. Premium American LeatherOur leather is USA vegetable tanned steer hide that is simply the best money can buy. We have a face-to-face relationship with our supplier, Hermann Oak Leather, who is based right here in our home town of St. Louis, Missouri. All the major parts of our sheaths are built with 11 ounce thick leather, which is difficult to work with in parts of the crafting process, but we love its iron-like durability. By the time we dye, tool, burnish and condition our leather it looks like a tank and will last like one too. Rugged Surface TextureOur leather is tooled with a rugged texture that is helpful for reducing glare and blending with a natural environment. If you need even more concealment, just rub on some dirt or charcoal before your mission. Wear your sheath with confidence and don't be afraid to scratch it up. The more adventures it has, the better it looks... and the more stories it will tell. Water Repellent FinishBefore leaving our workshop, every sheath is treated with our "Hedgehog Sheath Conditioner". This bees wax based, water repellent coating ensures your leather is ready for the elements the moment you take it out of the box. Superb FitWhen we build your sheath, we cut and form the parts around one of the actual knives we have in our workshop. That means it fits perfectly and will not be rattling around each time you take a step. If anything, we make them just a little tight because they all have a slight break-in period, just like a pair of hiking boots. Hedgehog sheaths are not generic, meaning that they are intended only for the knife we advertise them to be compatible with. For example, our sheath for the TOPS Fieldcraft Knife will not fit an Ontario Blackbird Knife and vice versa... even though different sheath models can look very similar in pictures. Double Row StitchingEvery Hedgehog sheath has a double row of high-strength stitching that pierces the three layers of leather that surround the knife. We use a double row for redundancy and because it creates a very rigid and secured welt in the area where the sharpened edge of the knife rests. This is essential in forming the sheath perfectly and eliminating movement when the knife is secured inside. Traditional Belt CarryOne way to wear this sheath is in a traditional vertical configuration hanging from the belt. Tie-Down HolesThis sheath also features four tie-down holes that are reinforced with metal grommets... that way you can improvise attachment positions for your specific needs. Our favorite way to carry this sheath is over the shoulder with a length of parachute cord strung through the lashing holes. This method excels in cold weather as it can be worn on top of a heavy coat. That means your knife is in easy reach and you keep your warmth inside the coat where it belongs, because you aren't lifting it to gain access to the sheath on your belt. AmbidextrousThis design is ambidextrous, meaning that it works equally well if you are right handed or left handed.
